<paragraph blockId="9.[264,1324,1649,1883]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">
<emphasis box="[264,430,1649,1674]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Spermathecae</emphasis>
: spermathecae globose with longitudinal axis equivalent to the length of sperm pump; spermathecal ducts 
<number box="[655,684,1689,1715]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" value="10.0">10</number>
times longer than sperm pump, uniting to form a short common spermathecal duct; sperm pump placed at nearly apical 
<number box="[1043,1054,1729,1755]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" value="1.0">1</number>
/ 
<number box="[1065,1080,1729,1755]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" value="5.0">5</number>
of the spermathecal duct; sclerotized collars of sperm pumps smaller on apical ends than on basal ones. (Fig. 
<number box="[1276,1308,1769,1795]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" value="17.0">17</number>
).
</paragraph>
